<Base title="Pure Crystal — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>Pure Crystal</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Galeria Promocyjna | 2021</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Explores the Atlantis myth and its contemporary relevance. "The story of the lost Atlantis is present in numerous cultural texts" and serves as a framework for examining modern mythologies. Plato originally used Atlantis as a cautionary tale about societal decline; today, online figures invoke similar narratives. The core inquiry addresses "fake news, conspiracy theories and neotribalism that proliferate in the web." Artists "display the non-time, fluidity, and reproducibility of online archetypes and myths," merging historical forms like pottery and textiles with internet aesthetics.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Artists:</strong> Kaja Redkie, Tomasz Mr&oacute;z, Filip Rybkowski, Ma&#322;gorzata Bi&#322;u&#324;ska, Karolina Jarz&#281;bak, Inside Job (Ula Luci&#324;ska, Micha&#322; Knychaus), Waldemar Borowski, Maciej Nowacki, Aleksandra Liput</p>
      <p><strong>Curators:</strong> Dzidy (Michalina Sablik, Aleksandra Liput)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
